com.github.blackjak34.compute.enums

Enum CharacterComputer

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<CharacterComputer>
      • com.github.blackjak34.compute.enums.CharacterComputer
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Comparable<CharacterComputer>

    public enum CharacterComputer
extends java.lang.Enum<CharacterComputer>
    An enum used for mapping ascii char code values returned from keypresses into uv coords that are used to find the corresponding character on the charset. Helper functions are included to allow retrieving ascii indexes/uv coords from the enums and retrieving enums from ascii codes.
    Since:
    1.0.1
    Author:
    Blackjak34

    • Field Detail

      • characters

        private static final java.util.HashMap<java.lang.Integer,CharacterComputer> characters
        A HashMap containing the character code for each character and its corresponding enum. Used for the getCharacter helper function.

      • charCode

        private final int charCode
        The ascii code that corresponds to this character.

      • uValue

        private final int uValue
        The u (x) element of the image's location on the charset texture. Divide this value by 16 to get a standard range from 0 to 1.

      • vValue

        private final int vValue
        The v (y) element of the image's location on the charset texture. Divide this value by 16 to get a standard range from 0 to 1.

        public int getUValue()

      • getCharacter

        public static CharacterComputer getCharacter(int charCode)
        Returns the character that corresponds to the given ascii code. If no character exists, the enum INVALID is returned instead.
        Parameters:
        charCode - An ascii code to get the enum for
        Returns:
        The enum corresponding to the given char code
